A sign of diabetes, very common with cats. They need insulin just like
humans if that is the case.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; I have had a few weak moments where I've ended up putting down salmon, ham
&gt; or chicken for him. He eats this very quickly and without complaint.
