Have you tried warming his food, a quick microwave zap, to release the
smell and flavour? It sometimes helps. Has anything changed about his food
bowl or its environment? I have had a cat that disliked a new plastic bowl
and eventually refused to eat from it. We thought at the time that he was
objecting to the food, but when we went back to his old battered stainless
steel bowl he was happy again and ate normally.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
