Try giving him a hard treat, and watch him while he eats it.  Does he
hesitate, take a long time about finishing it, or seem to favor one
side of his mouth?  My cat was doing this, and it turned out she had a
very painful cavity, but gave no other sign of discomfort - animals
can be so long-suffering.  Our vet pulled the tooth, and now she's
right as rain.

-Rushlight
